{"title":"Domestic Bomber is a steel cruiser bike that’s retro, modern & totally tubular","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/10/09/domestic-bomber-is-a-steel-cruiser-bike-thats-retro-modern-totally-tubular/","date":1633794569000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><img width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/09111206/domestic-bomber-steel-cruiser-coaster-brakes-1-800x600.jpg\" alt=\"domestic bomber steel city mountain bike\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/09111206/domestic-bomber-steel-cruiser-coaster-brakes-1-800x600.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/09111206/domestic-bomber-steel-cruiser-coaster-brakes-1-297x223.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/09111206/domestic-bomber-steel-cruiser-coaster-brakes-1-120x90.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/09111206/domestic-bomber-steel-cruiser-coaster-brakes-1-768x576.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/09111206/domestic-bomber-steel-cruiser-coaster-brakes-1-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/09111206/domestic-bomber-steel-cruiser-coaster-brakes-1.jpg 1600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"><header></header><p>Support us! BikeRumor may earn a small commission from affiliate links in this article. <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/privacy\" target=\"_blank\">Learn more</a>.</p></div><div role=\"main\"><article id=\"post-274192\" role=\"article\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/BlogPosting\"><section itemprop=\"text\"><p>The Domestic Bomber is a new steel-tubed cruiser bike from the small batch Nor-Cal builders that takes a modern look at retro components to future proof it. While it looks simple, there’s a LOT to appreciate on this rigid urban mountain bike worth looking at…</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/09111209/domestic-bomber-steel-cruiser-coaster-brakes-2.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/09111209/domestic-bomber-steel-cruiser-coaster-brakes-2.jpg\" alt=\"domestic bomber steel cruiser bicycle with coaster brakes\" width=\"1400\" height=\"1050\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/09111209/domestic-bomber-steel-cruiser-coaster-brakes-2.jpg 1400w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/09111209/domestic-bomber-steel-cruiser-coaster-brakes-2-297x223.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/09111209/domestic-bomber-steel-cruiser-coaster-brakes-2-800x600.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/09111209/domestic-bomber-steel-cruiser-coaster-brakes-2-120x90.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/09111209/domestic-bomber-steel-cruiser-coaster-brakes-2-768x576.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1400px) 100vw, 1400px\"></a></p><p>For starters, it’s a top shelf build, with a Sturmy Archer coaster brake hub and Basic cranks and components everywhere else.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/09111212/domestic-bomber-steel-cruiser-coaster-brakes-3.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/09111212/domestic-bomber-steel-cruiser-coaster-brakes-3.jpg\" alt=\"domestic bomber steel cruiser bicycle with coaster brakes\" width=\"1400\" height=\"1050\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/09111212/domestic-bomber-steel-cruiser-coaster-brakes-3.jpg 1400w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/09111212/domestic-bomber-steel-cruiser-coaster-brakes-3-297x223.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/09111212/domestic-bomber-steel-cruiser-coaster-brakes-3-800x600.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/09111212/domestic-bomber-steel-cruiser-coaster-brakes-3-120x90.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/09111212/domestic-bomber-steel-cruiser-coaster-brakes-3-768x576.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1400px) 100vw, 1400px\"></a></p><p>The frame is made of 4130 Chromoly steel, with oversized tubes for a bombproof (or bomber?) build, making it a great play bike for hucking off curbs or getting rowdy around town.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/09111217/domestic-bomber-steel-cruiser-coaster-brakes-6.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/09111217/domestic-bomber-steel-cruiser-coaster-brakes-6.jpg\" alt=\"domestic bomber steel cruiser bicycle with coaster brakes\" width=\"1420\" height=\"933\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/09111217/domestic-bomber-steel-cruiser-coaster-brakes-6.jpg 1420w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/09111217/domestic-bomber-steel-cruiser-coaster-brakes-6-297x195.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/09111217/domestic-bomber-steel-cruiser-coaster-brakes-6-800x526.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/09111217/domestic-bomber-steel-cruiser-coaster-brakes-6-120x79.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/09111217/domestic-bomber-steel-cruiser-coaster-brakes-6-768x505.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1420px) 100vw, 1420px\"></a></p><p>Up front is a Sturmy Archer drum brake hub, using the only cable seen on the bike with a single brake lever. And here’s where the bike starts to get really interesting…</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/09111229/domestic-bomber-steel-cruiser-coaster-brakes-12.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/09111229/domestic-bomber-steel-cruiser-coaster-brakes-12.jpg\" alt=\"domestic bomber steel cruiser bicycle with coaster brakes\" width=\"1200\" height=\"900\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/09111229/domestic-bomber-steel-cruiser-coaster-brakes-12.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/09111229/domestic-bomber-steel-cruiser-coaster-brakes-12-297x223.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/09111229/domestic-bomber-steel-cruiser-coaster-brakes-12-800x600.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/09111229/domestic-bomber-steel-cruiser-coaster-brakes-12-120x90.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/09111229/domestic-bomber-steel-cruiser-coaster-brakes-12-768x576.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"></a></p><p>The reaction arm (the part that sticks out of the hub) is affixed to the fork leg with an intentionally overbuilt adapter.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/09111214/domestic-bomber-steel-cruiser-coaster-brakes-4.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/09111214/domestic-bomber-steel-cruiser-coaster-brakes-4.jpg\" alt=\"domestic bomber steel cruiser bicycle with coaster brakes\" width=\"1625\" height=\"1066\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/09111214/domestic-bomber-steel-cruiser-coaster-brakes-4.jpg 1625w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/09111214/domestic-bomber-steel-cruiser-coaster-brakes-4-297x195.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/09111214/domestic-bomber-steel-cruiser-coaster-brakes-4-800x525.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/09111214/domestic-bomber-steel-cruiser-coaster-brakes-4-120x79.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/09111214/domestic-bomber-steel-cruiser-coaster-brakes-4-768x504.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/09111214/domestic-bomber-steel-cruiser-coaster-brakes-4-1536x1008.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1625px) 100vw, 1625px\"></a></p><p>The seat tube gets three water bottle bosses, arranged to hold an Anything Cage.</p><p>The point was to make the bike capable of using a small front hub e-bike motor to create an assisted version in the future. So, that little reaction arm is strong enough to handle the torque from a hub motor, and the Anything Cage is strong enough to hold a small battery pack.</p><p>The goal was to create a bike that could easily get up and down the hills of San Francisco for a commuter, then quickly convert to a normal pedal fun bike on the weekends.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/09111219/domestic-bomber-steel-cruiser-coaster-brakes-7.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/09111219/domestic-bomber-steel-cruiser-coaster-brakes-7.jpg\" alt=\"domestic bomber steel cruiser bicycle with coaster brakes\" width=\"1200\" height=\"900\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/09111219/domestic-bomber-steel-cruiser-coaster-brakes-7.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/09111219/domestic-bomber-steel-cruiser-coaster-brakes-7-297x223.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/09111219/domestic-bomber-steel-cruiser-coaster-brakes-7-800x600.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/09111219/domestic-bomber-steel-cruiser-coaster-brakes-7-120x90.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/09111219/domestic-bomber-steel-cruiser-coaster-brakes-7-768x576.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"></a></p><p>Tire clearance is a bit tight with bit mountain bike treads, but the stout frame should limit flex that would lead to tire rub (just don’t get anything caught in there…or run narrower tires).</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/09111222/domestic-bomber-steel-cruiser-coaster-brakes-8.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/09111222/domestic-bomber-steel-cruiser-coaster-brakes-8.jpg\" alt=\"domestic bomber steel cruiser bicycle with coaster brakes\" width=\"1400\" height=\"1050\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/09111222/domestic-bomber-steel-cruiser-coaster-brakes-8.jpg 1400w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/09111222/domestic-bomber-steel-cruiser-coaster-brakes-8-297x223.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/09111222/domestic-bomber-steel-cruiser-coaster-brakes-8-800x600.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/09111222/domestic-bomber-steel-cruiser-coaster-brakes-8-120x90.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/09111222/domestic-bomber-steel-cruiser-coaster-brakes-8-768x576.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1400px) 100vw, 1400px\"></a></p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/09111226/domestic-bomber-steel-cruiser-coaster-brakes-10.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/09111226/domestic-bomber-steel-cruiser-coaster-brakes-10.jpg\" alt=\"domestic bomber steel cruiser bicycle with coaster brakes\" width=\"1625\" height=\"600\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/09111226/domestic-bomber-steel-cruiser-coaster-brakes-10.jpg 1625w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/09111226/domestic-bomber-steel-cruiser-coaster-brakes-10-297x110.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/09111226/domestic-bomber-steel-cruiser-coaster-brakes-10-800x295.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/09111226/domestic-bomber-steel-cruiser-coaster-brakes-10-120x44.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/09111226/domestic-bomber-steel-cruiser-coaster-brakes-10-768x284.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/09111226/domestic-bomber-steel-cruiser-coaster-brakes-10-1536x567.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1625px) 100vw, 1625px\"></a></p><p>Price and availability? All they’re saying is “Coming Soon”, but you can follow them on social and more from their website to get on the list.</p><p><a href=\"https://domesticbikes.com/coming-soon/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>DomesticBikes.com</em></a></p></section></article></div></div>","author":"Tyler Benedict","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"ad1f958eac4fc5ef8f7579a8bb8f63e521c8407b673f3bb8a248f82d6bb32d58","category":"Cycling"}